<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="397" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1859,2030]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1860,1886]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name honors the late North American entomologist who described 
<taxonomicName authority=", Dr. Reece Ivan Sailer." authorityName="Dr. Reece Ivan Sailer." class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Alitocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1134,1244,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">Alitocoris</emphasis>
, Dr. Reece Ivan Sailer.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1859,2030]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1931,1958]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">Description.</emphasis>
Body oval, general color brown, punctures brown, usually confluent forming wrinkles. Antennae five-segmented. Gonocoxites VIII longer than wide, disc uniformly convex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1859,2030]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,153,1046]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">Head wider than long, declivous; vertex plain. Mandibular plates longer than clypeus, apart at apex, this round- ed and convergent; lateral margins reflected.Anteocular processes truncated. Antennal tubercles with a lateral spine. Antennae five-segmented. Ventrally with 1+1 carinae posterior to the eyes, concolor with the head. Bucculae with a small tooth on anterior angle, posteriorly evanescent. Labium reaching at least abdominal segment VI.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1046]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Pronotum wider than long, declivous. Cicatrices plain and punctured. Anterior margin concave; anterolateral margins slightly reflected; and posterior margin sinuous. Humeral angles not developed. Scutellum longer than wide, reaching connexival segment V; foveae black, flat and with punctures. Coria longer than scutellum. Pro-, meso-, and metapleura punctured, with yellowish maculae. Pro-, meso-, and metasternum black and punctured; prosternum furrowed, meso and metasternum with median carina. Mesopleural evaporatorium narrow following posterior margin of mesopleura; metapleural evaporatorium occupying half the width of metapleura, lateral margin subrectilinear; peritreme spout, reaching at least half the evaporatorium width. Tibiae dorsally sulcated; third segment of metatarsi dorsally depressed in females.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1046]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Connexivum exposed from segments III to VII. Abdomen with punctures, more concentrated on lateral margins, inconspicuous or absent on disc; longitudinal furrow shallow on median third from abdominal segment III to V. Trichobothria lateral to imaginary line tangential to spiracles; spiracles black, visible from abdominal segment II to VII.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1046]" box="[199,389,673,699]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1046]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">
Female. Genitalia. Gonocoxites VIII longer than wide, disc uniformly convex. Laterotergites VIII triangular, spiracles visible and posterior to lateral angle of gonocoxites VIII. Gonocoxites IX with median suture. Laterotergites IX digitiform, not surpassing the apex of laterotergites VIII (
<figureCitation box="[901,987,777,803]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1817,1842]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,179,1771]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1393,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–27. Female genital plates (ventroposterior view) and internal ducts. 21, 25 All. brunnea (Sailer) comb. nov.; 22, 26, All. poecila Garbelotto &amp; Campos sp. nov.; 23, All. ampla Garbelotto &amp; Campos sp. nov.; 24, 27 Sailerus maculosus (Sailer) comb. nov. Abbreviations: cm, conical microsculptures; cs, capsula seminalis; dr, ductus receptaculi; gcVIII, gonocoxites VIII; gcIX, gonocoxites IX; gpIX, gonapophyses IX; id, inner duct of vesicular area; laVIII, laterotergites VIII; laIX, laterotergites IX; md, median duct of vesicular area; od, outer duct of vesicular area; pi, pars intermedialis; rs, ring sclerites; tgIX, thickening of gonapophyses IX; vi, thickening of vaginal intima; VII, urosternite VII. Scale bars: 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235186/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Gonapophyses VIII and IX with folds bearing microsculptures (
<figureCitation box="[436,521,811,838]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1817,1842]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,179,1771]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1393,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–27. Female genital plates (ventroposterior view) and internal ducts. 21, 25 All. brunnea (Sailer) comb. nov.; 22, 26, All. poecila Garbelotto &amp; Campos sp. nov.; 23, All. ampla Garbelotto &amp; Campos sp. nov.; 24, 27 Sailerus maculosus (Sailer) comb. nov. Abbreviations: cm, conical microsculptures; cs, capsula seminalis; dr, ductus receptaculi; gcVIII, gonocoxites VIII; gcIX, gonocoxites IX; gpIX, gonapophyses IX; id, inner duct of vesicular area; laVIII, laterotergites VIII; laIX, laterotergites IX; md, median duct of vesicular area; od, outer duct of vesicular area; pi, pars intermedialis; rs, ring sclerites; tgIX, thickening of gonapophyses IX; vi, thickening of vaginal intima; VII, urosternite VII. Scale bars: 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235186/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="398" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1046]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,846,872]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Garbelotto &amp; Grazia &amp; Campos, 2019" authorityName="Garbelotto &amp; Grazia &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,414,846,872]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Sailerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,414,846,872]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Sailerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[421,527,846,872]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[421,527,846,872]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is monotypic and it is proposed based on the phylogeny of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[1239,1370,846,872]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Herrichella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1239,1370,846,872]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Herrichella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (
<bibRefCitation author="Garbelotto, T. A. &amp; Campos, L. A. &amp; Grazia, J." box="[159,411,881,907]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" pagination="452 - 472" refId="ref9489" refString="Garbelotto, T. A., Campos, L. A. &amp; Grazia, J. (2013) Cladistics and revision of Alitocoris with considerations on the phylogeny of the Herrichella clade (Hemiptera, Pentatomidae, Discocephalinae, Ochlerini). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 168, 452 - 472. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12032" type="journal article" year="2013">
Garbelotto 
<emphasis box="[287,343,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sailer, Loan From" authorityYear="1950" box="[429,593,881,907]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Alitocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosus">
<emphasis box="[429,593,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Ali. maculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grouped with 
<taxonomicName box="[755,911,881,907]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Alathetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufitarsis">
<emphasis box="[755,911,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Ala. rufitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a single synapomorphy, the lateral half of posterior margin of gonocoxites VIII projected posteriorly (character 48(2) of 
<bibRefCitation author="Garbelotto, T. A. &amp; Campos, L. A. &amp; Grazia, J." box="[1043,1300,915,942]" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" pagination="452 - 472" refId="ref9489" refString="Garbelotto, T. A., Campos, L. A. &amp; Grazia, J. (2013) Cladistics and revision of Alitocoris with considerations on the phylogeny of the Herrichella clade (Hemiptera, Pentatomidae, Discocephalinae, Ochlerini). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 168, 452 - 472. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12032" type="journal article" year="2013">
Garbelotto 
<emphasis box="[1171,1229,916,942]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
,). Apart this synapomorphy, 
<taxonomicName box="[330,486,950,976]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Alathetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufitarsis">
<emphasis box="[330,486,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Ala. rufitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sailer, Loan From" authorityYear="1950" box="[541,706,950,976]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Alitocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosus">
<emphasis box="[541,706,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Ali. maculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
present morphological differences (
<tableCitation box="[1111,1195,950,976]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="11.[151,239,1089,1113]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological differences between Alatethus rufitarsis Dallas, 1851 and Sailerus maculosus (Sailer, 1950) comb. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0C6657F122AE18C9BAD43FC14FF163" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" tableUuid="DF0C6657F122AE18C9BAD43FC14FF163">Table 1</tableCitation>
), and classifying 
<taxonomicName authority="in Alatethus" authorityName="in Alatethus" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Alitocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Ali. maculosus</emphasis>
in 
<emphasis box="[305,411,985,1011]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="398">Alatethus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would lead to rather loose genus boundaries.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
